Tum pooch rahe ho offline (internet ke bina) Git ko Eclipse mein kaise use kare.

Offline ka matlab 👉 sirf local computer par version control use karna.

Follow karo 👇


---

✅ 1️⃣ Eclipse mein local Git repository banana

1. Eclipse open karo


2. Project par Right Click


3. Team → Share Project


4. Select Git


5. Click Create Repository


6. Finish



👉 Ab project Git control mein aa gaya (offline).


---

✅ 2️⃣ Changes save & commit karna (offline)

1. File edit karo


2. Right click project → Team → Commit


3. Message likho


4. Click Commit



👉 Ye commit sirf local system mein save hota hai.


---

✅ 3️⃣ Project history dekhna

Right click project →
Team → Show in History

👉 Tum purane versions dekh sakte ho.


---

✅ 4️⃣ Previous version wapas lana

1. History open karo


2. Kisi old commit par right click


3. Reset → Hard / Mixed



👉 Purana version restore ho jayega.


---

🔥 Offline Git ka use kyu useful hai?

✔ Code backup rehta hai
✔ Galti ho jaaye to revert kar sakte ho
✔ Version history milti hai
✔ Internet ki zarurat nahi


---

⚠️ Online kab chahiye?

Sirf tab jab: ✅ GitHub par upload karna ho
✅ Team ke saath share karna ho


